 <text id="B0563T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>How alerts Brown to his upcoming tour to Staunton and the upper portion of his district.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr>
      <abbr expan="Orlando">O.</abbr> Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">A.C.</abbr></name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1866-02-14"><abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> 14th 1866</date>
      <name type="place">
       <abbr expan="Richmond, Virginia">Richd, Va</abbr>
      </name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Colonel</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>I have the honor to inform you that I shall start today on a tour through the upper portion
     of my District reaching Staunton, probably, on the 17th of the month, and respectfully request
     that any business requiring immediate attention may be directed to me at that place until about
     the 24th of this month.</p>

    <p><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr>
     <abbr expan="George">G.</abbr> W. Wells, <abbr expan="Assistant Quartermaster">AQM</abbr>
     &amp; <abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">
      <add hand="h1" place="inline">A</add> Supt.</abbr> will transact the
     <unclear>ordinary</unclear> office business during my absence. </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>I am &amp;c</salute>
     <signed><abbr expan="W. Storer How">W.S.H.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr>
      &amp;c</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
